  <text>
     <body>
     <div type="encomium">
   <l>LOok on the <hi>Glasse</hi> of mans <hi>Mortalitie:</hi>
   </l>
   <l>Behold the <hi>Mirrour</hi> of <hi>Eternitie.</hi>
   </l>
   <l>This <hi>Book</hi> is both; Herein behold thy face;</l>
   <l>It waxeth old; thy <hi>Glasse</hi> doth runne apace.</l>
   <l>It is appointed all men once to die;</l>
   <l>And after <hi>death</hi> succeeds <hi>Eternitie.</hi>
   </l>
   <l>This <hi>Life's</hi> no <hi>Life,</hi> which <hi>Time</hi> doth comprehend</l>
   <l>But that's true Life indeed, which knows no end▪</l>
   <l>This <hi>Book</hi> will teach thee so to <hi>live</hi> and <hi>die,</hi>
   </l>
   <l>That thou maist <hi>live</hi> unto <hi>Eternitie.</hi>
   </l>
   <signed>Thomas Gouge.</signed>
</div>
